WARNER SUGAR REFINING COMPANY, Libelant-Appellee, v. MUNSON STEAMSHIP LINE, Respondent-Appellant. MUNSON STEAMSHIP LINE, Cross-Libelant-Appellant, v. WARNER SUGAR REFINING COMPANY, Cross-Respondent-Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 20, 1929. No. 342. Bigham, Englar, Jones & Houston, of New York City (Henry N. Longley, F. Herbert Prem, and Roger H. Loughran, all of New York City, of counsel), for libelant cross-respondent. Kirlin, Woolsey, Campbell, Hickox & Keating, of New York City (L. De Grove Potter and Earl Appleman, both of New York City, of counsel), for respondent and oross-libelant.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (23 F.(2d) 194) affirmed.
